                    <tr>
           	<td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">
                      <font face="arial" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> here's a post i made in response to a mage in my guild who feels that "necros should be twitching over long fights so my clerics can heal more/longer".. we're discussing a fight we had with the idol of zek unslowed as aow practice.. i think the parse in question we got him to 40%, i wasn't there.. but a bard had other hits on and parsed the whole fight, which was going swell till all our clerics ran oom. but regardless, if any tard asks you to spend all yer <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> twitching because it's somehow best for the team, here's what i say: <br /><br />*************<br /><br />i think it's pretty clear that you underestimate the value of dps. let's take a look: <br /><br />verser parsed the idol at 835 dps. the fight lasted 4:31. we healed 226,481 hp. my <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> pool is 3300, and i regen <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> at 35(al)+7(sp)+7(ft)+13(bard)=62/tick standing. the fight lasted 45 ticks, so i would regen 2790 <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> during that time, making my available <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> pool for the fight 6090. <br /><br />case 1: twitchin:<br />so let's say i spend all my <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> twitching cause i wanna be a team player. both twitch spells are roughly a 3:1 ratio, so assuming i get some decent rolls on spec i can transfer ~3000 <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> in that time. let's also pretend that i spread it out perfectly across the ch chain. I believe the chain was set to ch every 2 seconds, so assuming that ch actually costs each cleric about 300 (i'll be generous) <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> to cast after spec checks, that's 10 more ch's that can land before they run outa <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite">. the ma will live an additional 20 seconds because i'm a battery. <br /><br />for the sake of argument, let's say that the idol had just enough hp to make those 20 seconds the difference in the fight, and he dies and we all are oom at the exacty time he eats it. so twitching was a good idea right? let's see. <br /><br />verser has the idol taking 200k in melee damage during that 4:31, and for the sake of argument let's not take the nukers into account, since we can't really judge what their output was, and it would only correspondingly raise the idol's hp in our little example here. i'm pretty sure we can get away with it without breaking our example, which leads us to: <br /><br />case 2: snag does damage:<br /><br />6090 <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> for a 4:31 fight. <br /><br />4 funeral pyres in 4 minutes: 2160X4 = 8640 for 1800 <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> (it's alteration so we'll call it 1500)<br /><br />3 splurts in 4:30: 4800 for 711 <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> (also alt, so we'll say 500)<br /><br />2 pyrocurors in 4 minutes: 4k damage for 800 <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> (alt, we'll say 600)<br /><br />4 cessation of cor's in 4 min: 4k damage for 1k <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> (alt, 800 <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite">)<br /><br />vexing mordania 2x over that time: 2k damage for 1k <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite">, (alt, 800 <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite">)<br /><br />let's see, that brings dot damage up to: <br /><br />23,440 damage for 4200 <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite">, leaving almost 3k <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> for nukes: <br />4x touch of night (average ~800)= 3200 for about 1400 <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite">, 1600 not counting specs. <br /><br />so let's call that close enough, and see how much shorter the idol's life would have been without that extra 26,640 hp. <br /><br />the fight lasted 271 seconds, and we did 195,161 damage to him in that time. this puts our dps at 720 (assuming dps is damage/seconds)... again it's actually higher than that, but so is the true value of the hp damage we did to it, so they should cancel each other out. <br /><br />assuming my math is right, it would have taken us an extra 37 seconds to make up for the damage i theoretically did. pretty obviously, my dps is worth twice as much as my twitching. I would rather have a fight last 37 seconds shorter than baseline rather than extend a fight for 20 seconds but have to make up for all my lost damage. this goes doubly for any fight where we have to worry about healing rampage tanks, ae damage, or any other kind of non-ma damage. higher dps = shorter fights = better for everyone. <br /><br />so you see, long fights are no different than any other. twitch is massively, horribly, and unspeakably <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite">-inefficient. i know it sounds good on paper that being able to heal for a tiny bit longer is best for the encounter, but it obviously isn't. <br /><br />and don't forget my original point, that mind wrack creates <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> out of nothing, actually gives each necro doing it more <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> than it costs, and is easy done. to give a quickie comparison: <br /><br />twitch: ~3k <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> delivered with a 8 second dly recast time spell over 4:31. <br /><br />mind wrack: 9 casts of mw, each netting 300 <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> for every person in group: 2700 x 6 = 24,300 <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> <--- not a typo. and it's *free*. i can do all my dps i want while doing it, and so can all the other necros. <br /><br />it's a fallacy to think that twitching is anything but a bad idea in most situations outside of buff/coh cycles. it's silly to poo-poo a necro's dps because 'cleric <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite">' has a mystique of being more important. unless i've made some gross math error, necro dps is much more useful than our pitiful 3:1 ratio twitches.<br /><br /><table><tr><td><img src="http://xena.ipns.com/~snag/dave/snagsig.jpg"></td><td align=center><br />-Lich Snag Bowskey <br><br />-Baron Paindemic clrbot</td></tr></table><br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=77614" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=77614</a></span id="msg"></font>
           	</td>
                    </tr>
