                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Quote<br /><br />so let's call that close enough, and see how much shorter the idol's life would have been without that extra 26,640 hp. <br /><br />the fight lasted 271 seconds, and we did 195,161 damage to him in that time. this puts our dps at 720 (assuming dps is damage/seconds)... again it's actually higher than that, but so is the true value of the hp damage we did to it, so they should cancel each other out. <br /><br />End Quote<br /><br />This is an error in logic. If the nukers were doing an equal amount of damage then the raid would have had a 1440/DPS and would have needed 18.5 seconds to inflict as much damage as your necro. Your numbers would prove that Twicthing extended the raids life for a second and a half beyond your DPS. This is the exact opposite of your conclusion. If I am mistaken please elaborate.<br /><br />Second these numbers represent a high level overview of damage and twitching and they do not examine why CH chains go OOM. Lets apply an eye cleric <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> regen over the course of a fight.<br /><br />Assume a cleric with 3500 <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> 1 standing regen FT 10 SP 7 KEI 13 Bard 13 gets 44/<span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> a tick. Further assume 150 per minute from medding (This cleric has a horsie.) Plus 60 <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> per minute from Mage rods. Casting 2 1/2 CH per minue, 6 man cleric rotation 4 second delay, this cleric uses about 200 <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> per minute. He can maintain the CH rotation 16.5 minutes. A single twitch per minute will extend this cleric's CH lifecycle to 70 minutes.<br /><br />Now assume a weaker cleric with 2800 <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> 0 FT and no horse. He regens 34 <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> a tick with maybe 80 <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> a minute from medding. He loses, in the same rotation, 370 <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> per minute. He can maintain this pace for about 7.5 minutes. A single twitch per minute increases his lifecycle to 12.7 minutes.<br /><br />If we accept these numbers how can anyone argue the power of twitching? If a raid had 4 strong clerics and 2 weak clerics a single necro could extend the lifecycle of the CH rotation by 5.2 minutes. During this time a raid with a 720/DPS would inflict 224,640 points of damage. <br /><br />Granted necros have an extremely high DPS. In fact we can outdamage most people in our guilds. However to turn our backs on something unique to our class and has such a dramatic effect on a raid does not seem logical to me.<br /><br /><br />Whar Necro of Test<br /><br />Edited by - Whar on 10/20/2002  14:11:10</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
