                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> thanks asmar and whar, i see your points. <br /><br />asmar, i tried to be generous twitch wise, by claiming i could transfer 3k <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> with my 6090 <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite">, resulting in nearly a 2:1 ratio all told. i'm not really sure how many times i could twitch on a full bar, but my guess is that i would end up transferring less than 3k <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> give 6090, including fizzles and whatnot. maybe i'll get off my ass and see someday.. <br /><br />whar, thanks for the clarification.. i'll try to explain and hopefully i didn't mess up the math :D <br /><br />if we assume the casters were also at 720 dps (would surprise me), then the total damage they did was also 200k.<br /><br />i think i failed to mention the 3 scenarios i was thinking of.. since the fight parse i was using ended when the idol was 40%, i'm kind of using it to simply make up fights that go along the same lines damage wise. <br /><br />case 1: snag isn't there, and the healing runs out at 4:31 and everyone dies. <br />case 2: snag is there, and twitches like a mofaka, extending the fight 20 seconds. <br />case 3: snag is there in normal form, and the fight ends 37 seconds earlier than case 1. <br /><br />now i did arrive at those numbers by ignoring casters, so let's make up some numbers and toss em in and see what happens. <br /><br />if we assume 720dps for melees and casters, then case 1 ends with 400k damage done, but the same damage absorbed. i also assumed that in case 2, my twitching was just barely enough for us to win the fight just as everyone ran oom. my twitching would have allowed for an additional 20 seconds for the ch chain, so if we assume no one dies before the ma, the guild is running at 1440 dps (not counting me), and in that extra time can do 28,800 damage. so our hypothetical idol has exactly 428,800 hp to be done away with. <br /><br />so we hop to case 3: i do 26k or so in damage, and 7k from lifeburn (assuming the dot wears off), for a total of 33k. i sorta forgot about lb in my first post, so hell i'll toss it in now. if we picture the 3 scenarios on a timeline, we get:<br /><br /><br />******************3*1**2<br /><br />each number marking the point in time the fight ends. even with what i think of as an inflated guild dps figure (at least for my guild), the efficiency of damage on the front end outweighs the ability to slightly extend the healing on the back end. <br /><br />of course, these figures don't take into account things like rampage healing, ae, or other 'atrrition' type fights where dps and shorter fights have an even bigger advantage, but whar's point is well made.. the higher the guild dps, the less significant my chunk of it is, whereas the healing (at least in bonehead 1-tank healing yawnfest fights), remains a constant rate over time. there definitely is a conversion point where my dps would be less than what i could allow the guild to do by twitching and extending the fight. given the efficiency of our dots and twitches, i don't really see that happening anytime soon though. <br /><br />maybe i should get off my ass and test it out, but it varies greatly depending mostly on the relative share of dps that the necro represents. <br /><br />at any rate the point is moot for me, mind wrack is crack compared to the paint-huffing that is twitching, and with few exceptions i expect to be able to use that to help with <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite">, keeping those effing clerics so happy i never hear that word again..<br /><br /><table><tr><td><img src="http://xena.ipns.com/~snag/dave/snagsig.jpg"></td><td align=center><br />-Lich Snag Bowskey <br><br />-Baron Paindemic clrbot</td></tr></table><br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=77614" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=77614</a></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
