                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Snag - to strengthen your argument<br /><br />when we DOT the fight is shorter,   time = T<br />When we twitch the fight is longer, time = T + DELTA.<br /><br />While the mob is alive it will regen. When we twitch it lives longer so the regen in the period DETLA needs to be added back onto the twitching figures. So making them WORSE. in your example<br /><br />DELTA = something like 37 seconds - actully quite a bit more maybe 50secs in the end but anyway just using 37 secs.<br /><br />37secs / 6 * regen per tick = 6 * 5k?? = 30K more dmg that the twitch has to account for. So making the twitch figures worse. (I dunno if 5k per tick is right)<br /><br /><br />Notes<br /><br />1) I am NOT saying that DOTS and disease DOTS stop REGEN. I KNOW that they do NOT stop regen. But if the fight is SHORTER then the regen in period which DOTing shortens the fight needs to be accounted for when coming up with twicthing times. <br /><br />2) The maths is hard to do so an approximation is fine.<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Edited by - culmore on 10/21/2002  06:40:25</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
