                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Good info.<br /><br />With Whar's comments about the effect of the caster damage skewing the picture to make twitching more useful, it becomes muddier, but the info is there.<br /><br />Remember that as HP of the mobs goes up (see Luclin), the healer's <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> becomes more important and the difference from your top clerics (<span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> regen wise) compared to your lowest clerics becomes a bigger issue.  A few twitches to the lowest <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> regen clerics extends the chain a good while.  If all clerics are equal in <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> regen, then yes twitching is a lot less useful.  It's good to fill in a weak link, not as a replacement for healer <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite">.<br /><br />Also remember that as AC of the mobs go up (see Luclin) caster damage becomes the primary source of damage and your contribution as DPS becomes more important... all of these factors way in... each encounter is different.<br /><br />Sometimes it IS best to twitch.  It's not the hero's job, it's not a fun job, but it is best for the raid.<br /><br />Basically it depends on the encounter and the raid party you bring to fight it.<br /><br />A 100% resist mob makes an easy case for twitching.<br /><br />A high AC, low HP mob and a raid with extra clerics makes an easy case for Damage.<br /><br />Learning where to draw the line between them is a tricky thing, that's slowly learned.  From my personal experience, I see it falling usually in the way of DPS, but there have been times when twitches have saved the day, and my DPS would not have.  <br /><br />The exact example I'm thinking of was an AoW attempt with 8 clerics and two new to the guild clerics with low <span class="spnSearchHighlight" id="hilite">mana</span id="hilite"> regen running LoM as our mage was LD.  I removed two dots from my scheme, and did one twitch per minute to each of them.  I believe it made the difference.<br /><br />One final comment on the comment that casting that many DoTs will cause you to be summoned and killed.  I'll respond with an answer instead of a smug "you need to learn how".  The answer is of course FD.<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Therros Rex'Necri<br />Tier'Dal Warlock<br />Tarew Marr</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
